race.description: Lake Cathie Netball Club Maiden Plate (C1)
race.comment: HIGHLAND HUSTLE (5) is racing in career-best form, highlighted by a huge maiden win over the mile at Coffs Harbour two back. Won't mind the step up in distance. Going better than most of these and another win looks on the cards. EINSTEIN'S THEORY (7) showed a glimpse of form last time out, making late inroads to finish fifth at the end of 1500m at this circuit. Peaking now after three runs back and the slightly longer trip is a tick. DEVOTED TO YOU (9) settled back in the field and struggled to make ground when she last appeared over 1400m at Taree. Looking for this sort of journey now so a better run is anticipated. Forget the last result of HEART OF PLATINUM (4) as 1200m was way too short. Beaten just 2.1 lengths here at this trip three back which is a better pointer to her chances. HARDASH (1) next best in a race that lacks depth.
